# =============================================================================
# squid Configuration Example
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env and update with your settings
# Choose ONE of the configurations below based on your LLM provider

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logging Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
LOG_LEVEL=error
DB_LOG_LEVEL=debug
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Context Window Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Maximum context window size in tokens (global default)
# This enables accurate token usage tracking and prevents exceeding model limits
# Default: 8192 tokens if not specified
# Note: Individual agents can override this in squid.config.json with their own context_window setting
# Example in squid.config.json:
#   "agents": {
#     "general-assistant": {
#       "model": "qwen3.5-4b",
#       "context_window": 32768,
#       ...
#     }
#   }
SQUID_CONTEXT_WINDOW=32768

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DEPRECATED: API_MODEL
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API_MODEL is deprecated as of v0.12.0
# CLI commands (ask, review) now use the default agent's model from squid.config.json
# Web UI always used agent-specific models
# You can safely remove API_MODEL from your configuration

# =============================================================================
# OPTION 1: LM Studio (Recommended for Local Development)
# =============================================================================
# 1. Download LM Studio from https://lmstudio.ai/
# 2. Download model: lmstudio-community/Qwen2.5-Coder-7B-Instruct-MLX-4bit
# 3. Load the model in LM Studio
# 4. Start local server (↔️ icon → "Start Server")
# 5. Use these settings:

API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1
# API_MODEL=local-model  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models in squid.config.json
API_KEY=not-needed
# SQUID_CONTEXT_WINDOW=32768  # Qwen2.5-Coder default

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTION 2: Docker Model Runner (Docker Desktop/Engine)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Enable Docker Model Runner:
#    - Docker Desktop: Settings → AI → Enable "Docker Model Runner"
#    - Docker Engine: sudo apt-get install docker-model-plugin (Ubuntu/Debian)
#                      sudo dnf install docker-model-plugin (RPM-based)
# 2. Pull models:
#    docker model pull hf.co/bartowski/Qwen2.5-Coder-7B-Instruct-GGUF:Q4_K_M
#    docker model pull hf.co/nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5-GGUF  # For RAG
# 3. Verify: docker model ls
# 4. Use these settings:

# API_URL=http://localhost:12434/engines/v1
# API_MODEL=huggingface.co/bartowski/qwen2.5-coder-7b-instruct-gguf:Q4_K_M  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models
# API_KEY=not-needed
# SQUID_CONTEXT_WINDOW=32768  # Qwen2.5-Coder: 32K tokens

# Alternative chat/completion models (DEPRECATED - configure in squid.config.json agents instead):
# API_MODEL=huggingface.co/bartowski/qwen2.5-coder-1.5b-instruct-gguf:Q4_K_M  # Smaller (~1GB, 32K context)
# API_MODEL=ai/qwen3-coder                                                     # Latest Qwen3 from Docker Hub
# API_MODEL=docker.io/ai/smollm2:latest                                        # Lightweight (~256MB, 4K context)

# RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) Configuration:
# If you want to use RAG features, also configure these settings in squid.config.json:
# {
#   "rag": {
#     "enabled": true,
#     "embedding_model": "huggingface.co/nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5-gguf:latest",
#     "embedding_url": "http://localhost:12434/engines/v1",
#     "chunk_size": 512,
#     "chunk_overlap": 50,
#     "top_k": 5,
#     "documents_path": "documents"
#   }
# }

# Important notes:
# - Use bartowski's GGUF models for chat (single-file format, no split issues)
# - Avoid official Qwen GGUF models (they're split into multiple files)
# - Embedding model is separate - pull it for RAG document search features
# - Model IDs are lowercase with full domain (e.g., huggingface.co/...)
# - The /engines/v1 path is required for OpenAI SDK compatibility

# Search for more models:
# docker model search qwen2.5-coder
# docker model search bartowski
# docker model search nomic-embed

# Docker Desktop: Port defaults to 12434 (configurable in Settings → AI)
# Docker Engine: Port is always 12434

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTION 3: Ollama (Lightweight CLI Alternative)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Install: brew install ollama (macOS) or see https://ollama.com/
# 2. Start service: ollama serve
# 3. Pull model: ollama pull qwen2.5-coder
# 4. Use these settings:

# API_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# API_MODEL=qwen2.5-coder  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models in squid.config.json
# API_KEY=not-needed
# SQUID_CONTEXT_WINDOW=32768  # Qwen2.5-Coder: 32K tokens

# Alternative Ollama models (DEPRECATED - configure in squid.config.json agents instead):
# API_MODEL=codellama          # Code generation focused (16K context)
# API_MODEL=deepseek-coder     # Code understanding (16K context)
# API_MODEL=llama3.1           # General purpose (128K context)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTION 4: OpenAI API (Cloud Service)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Get API key from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# 2. Add credits to your account
# 3. Use these settings:

# API_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# API_MODEL=gpt-4  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models in squid.config.json
# API_KEY=sk-your-actual-api-key-here
# SQUID_CONTEXT_WINDOW=128000  # GPT-4: 128K tokens

# Alternative OpenAI models (DEPRECATED - configure in squid.config.json agents instead):
# API_MODEL=gpt-4-turbo        # Faster, cheaper GPT-4 (128K context)
# API_MODEL=gpt-3.5-turbo      # Fastest, cheapest (16K context)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTION 5: Mistral API (Cloud Service)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Get API key from https://console.mistral.ai/
# 2. Choose a model (devstral-2512, mistral-large-latest, etc.)
# 3. Use these settings:

# API_URL=https://api.mistral.ai/v1
# API_MODEL=devstral-2512  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models in squid.config.json
# API_KEY=your-mistral-api-key-here
# SQUID_CONTEXT_WINDOW=131072  # Mistral Large: 128K tokens

# Alternative Mistral models (DEPRECATED - configure in squid.config.json agents instead):
# API_MODEL=mistral-large-latest    # Most capable (128K context)
# API_MODEL=mistral-small-latest    # Fast and efficient (32K context)
# API_MODEL=codestral-latest        # Code-specialized (32K context)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTION 6: Other OpenAI-Compatible Services
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# OpenRouter (https://openrouter.ai/)
# API_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# API_MODEL=anthropic/claude-3-sonnet  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models in squid.config.json
# API_KEY=your-openrouter-key

# Together AI (https://together.ai/)
# API_URL=https://api.together.xyz/v1
# API_MODEL=codellama/CodeLlama-34b-Instruct-hf  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models in squid.config.json
# API_KEY=your-together-ai-key

# Custom OpenAI-compatible endpoint
# API_URL=http://your-custom-endpoint:port/v1
# API_MODEL=your-model-name  # DEPRECATED: Use agent-specific models in squid.config.json
# API_KEY=your-api-key-if-needed

# =============================================================================
# Common Context Window Sizes
# =============================================================================
# Qwen2.5-Coder-7B:  32768   (32K tokens)
# GPT-4/GPT-4o:      128000  (128K tokens)
# GPT-3.5-turbo:     16385   (16K tokens)
# Claude 3 Opus:     200000  (200K tokens)
# Claude 3.5 Sonnet: 200000  (200K tokens)
# Llama 3.1-8B:      131072  (128K tokens)
# Mistral Large:     131072  (128K tokens)
# DeepSeek Coder:    16384   (16K tokens)
# CodeLlama:         16384   (16K tokens)
#
# How to find your model's context window:
# 1. Check model documentation on Hugging Face
# 2. Look in the model card or config.json
# 3. Check your LLM provider's documentation
# 4. For LM Studio: Look at model details in the UI

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
# - Only ONE configuration should be active (uncomment the one you want)
# - LM Studio and Ollama don't require API keys (use "not-needed")
# - For best code-related results, use qwen2.5-coder model
# - Streaming is supported with all providers (use -s or --stream flag)
# - Set SQUID_CONTEXT_WINDOW to match your model for accurate usage tracking
